gov.noaa.ncdc.crn.domain.sort
Class StationComparator<T>

java.lang.Object
  gov.noaa.ncdc.crn.domain.sort.StationComparator<T>
Type Parameters:
T - supports Station or Integer
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.util.Comparator<T>
public class StationComparator<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Comparator<T>, java.io.Serializable

Comparator for sorting List and List of stationIds Sample usage where stationDao is an instance of an implementation of StationDao: Map stationMap = stationDao.getStations(); List stations = new ArrayList(); stations.addAll(stationMap.values()); // sorts by station name (state,location,vector) using Station.compareTo(Station); Collections.sort(stations); // sorts all stations by goesid Collections.sort(stations, new StationComparator(StationComparator.SORTS.GOES_ID)); List stationIds = new ArrayList(); stationIds.addAll(stationMap.keySet()); // sorts stationIds first by networkId and then by stationId Collections.sort(stationIds, new StationComparator(stationMap,StationComparator.SORTS.NETWORK_ID,StationComparator.SORTS.STATION_ID));

Author:
Andrea Fey

StationComparator

public StationComparator(java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,Station> stationMap,
                         StationComparator.SORTS... sorts)
Constructor which uses stationMap lookup. Can be used for StationComparator construction where the Integer is assumed to be a stationId referencing a particular Station. All SORTS are supported with this constructor. When parameters are station ids, compares Stations retrieved from station map.

Parameters:
stationMap - non-null Map lookup for Stations by stationId
sorts - indicates sort order; sorts applied in argument order

compare

public static int compare(Station a,
                          Station b,
                          StationComparator.SORTS sort)
Compares its first two argument Stations for order based on the sorting strategy indicated by its third argument. Returns a negative integer, zero, or a positive integer as the first Station is less than, equal to, or greater than the second based on the sorting strategy.

Parameters:
a - - the first Station to be compared.
b - - the second Station to be compared.
sort - - the sorting strategy to use for comparison
Returns:
a negative integer, zero, or a positive integer as the first argument is less than, equal to, or greater than the second based on the sorting strategy.
Throws:
java.lang.ClassCastException - - if the arguments' types prevent them from being compared
